Colour when fresh, silvery grey, gradually changing to dark brown with purplish tinge from about pelvic-fin insertion posteriorly (
Fig. 1
). Jaws black, iris silvery. Fins pale, except for black, square to semi-circular spot on proximal part of middle caudal-fin rays.

Distribution. This species is currently known only from the type specimens, four of which were collected east of New South Wales , Australia , and the remaining three in the EEZ of New Zealand (
Fig. 2
).
